# React Native Data Fetching with tRPC v10

## Overview

This guide describes the comprehensive data fetching architecture using tRPC v10 with `@trpc/react-query` for React Native Expo SDK 54 applications. The mobile app connects to the monorepo backend via end-to-end typesafe tRPC procedures, with MMKV persistence for offline-first capabilities.

**Authentication**: For Supabase authentication setup, session management, and secure storage, see the [Supabase Authentication & Storage Guide](./506-react-native-supabase-authentication-and-storage.mdc).

## Installed Dependencies

All required packages are installed in `apps/mobile/package.json`:

- `@trpc/client` v10.45.2 - tRPC client core
- `@trpc/react-query` v10.45.2 - React Query integration for tRPC
- `@tanstack/react-query` v5.90.5 - Underlying query library
- `@scani/backend` workspace:\* - Backend workspace for AppRouter types
- `lucide-react-native` v0.552.0 - Icon library for loading states
- `react-native-mmkv` v3.3.3 - Fast persistent storage
- `expo-network` (Expo SDK 54) - Network state detection

